import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['population'], data['engineers'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the population and number of engineers in each state?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Population')
    plt.ylabel('Engineers')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data = data.sort_values(by='engineers', ascending=False)
    ax = plt.bar(data['state'], data['engineers'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('Which state has the highest percentage of engineers?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=data['engineers'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max percentage of engineers: {:.2f}'.format(data['engineers'].max()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
